About Me

Hi, I am a Data Science and Biostatistics Masters student in Columbia University, graduating in October 2022.
My journey to data science has started from being heavily involved with computational neuroscience research
in undergraduate and post-graduate, where I was able to really confirm my passion for analyzing data
and turning them into meaningful insights. This led me to my current graduate program, where I have not only
learned about data science and statistics in depth, but also have gotten a lot of hands-on experience through projects
and work experience through internships. Please check out some of my data science projects!
